<title>HONG KONG: Tianjin Bohai sets term loan.</title>
<headline>Tianjin Bohai sets term loan.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following syndicated loan</p>
<p>was announced by the coordinating arrangers.</p>
<p> BORROWER    TIANJIN BOHAI CHEMICAL INDUSTRY (GROUP) CO LTD</p>
<p> AMOUNT	UP TO US$30 MLN  TYPE	 TERM LOAN</p>
<p> MARGIN	3 OR 6ML+130BP   MATURITY   5 YRS</p>
<p> PUTS	  YR 3		 CALL	 YR 3</p>
<p> DRAWDOWN    MULTIPLE	   AVAIL	12 MTHS</p>
<p> REPAYMENT   8 EQUAL SEMI-ANNUAL INSTALMENTS AFTER 18 MONTHS</p>
<p>		 GRACE PERIOD</p>
<p> GOV LAW     CHINA/HONGKONG   TAX PROV   FREE &amp; CLEAR</p>
<p> COORDINATING ARRANGERS   BNP HONG KONG AND CCIF FINANCE</p>
<p> ARRANGERS		    BANK OF CHINA'S TIANJIN BRANCH,</p>
<p>				  SUMITOMO BANK AND WESTDEUTSCHE</p>
<p>				  LANDESBANK.</p>
<p>MGT LEVELS AND FEES</p>
<p>PREPAYMENT FEE OF 0.125 PCT FLAT</p>
<p>COMMITMENT FEE OF 0.35 PCT PER ANNUM</p>
<p> SENIOR MANAGERS     US$4-5 MLN    25BP</p>
<p> MANAGERS		US$3 MLN	20BP</p>
<p> NOTES   PROCEEDS WILL BE USED TO FINANCE THE MEDIUM TERM</p>
<p>	   GENERAL CORPORATE FUNDING PURPOSES</p>
<p>	   A LETTER OF SUPPORT FROM TIANJIN MUNICIPAL PEOPLE'S</p>
<p>	   GOVERNMENT</p>
<p>	   ** THE BORROWER SHALL BE BENEFICALLY OWNED AT LEAST 60</p>
<p>	   PCT BY THE TIANJIN BOHAI CHEMICAL INDUSTRY GROUP CORP</p>
<p>	   AND AT LEAST 50 PCT BY THE TIANJIN MUNICIPAL PEOPLE'S</p>
<p>	   GOV'T</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6960</p>
